üöÄ Understanding Composition, Recomposition, and Disposal in Jetpack Compose üéØ

Jetpack Compose introduces a powerful declarative UI model ‚Äî but to truly harness its potential, it's important to understand the lifecycle of Composables:

‚úÖ Composition ‚Äì This is where it all begins! Composables are first inserted into the UI tree.
‚úÖ Recomposition ‚Äì When state changes, only the affected Composables are redrawn ‚Äî efficiently updating the UI.
‚úÖ Disposal ‚Äì When a Composable leaves the screen or becomes irrelevant, it is removed from the Composition, freeing up resources.

üîç Each stage plays a vital role in performance, memory management, and responsiveness in modern Android apps.

üìä Here's a simple visual I created to make these concepts easier to grasp.
